</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="45.[151,1436,512,755]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,300,585,611]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Ecology.</emphasis>
Recorded in 
<collectingCountry box="[457,552,585,611]" name="Portugal" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Portugal</collectingCountry>
from a flower-rich meadow in Mediterranean shrubland, a river margin of a Mediterranean nature, and a mixed forest / orchard. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1809" box="[734,926,621,647]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Ortochile" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigrocoerulea">
<emphasis box="[734,926,621,647]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">O. nigrocoerulea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, like other species of this genus, is a frequent flower visitor, where it is most often observed.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="45.[151,1436,512,755]" box="[199,456,692,719]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">
